placementdrives.companyDescription: Google LLC is an American multinational technology company focusing on AI, online advertising, and cloud computing.
placementdrives.jobDescription: Design and develop scalable systems for Google products used by billions.

placementdrives.companyDescription: Microsoft Corporation develops, licenses, and sells computer software, consumer electronics, and personal computers.
placementdrives.jobDescription: Build products that millions of people use every day in Azure, Office, and Windows.

placementdrives.companyDescription: Amazon.com, Inc. is an American multinational technology company focusing on e-commerce, cloud computing, and AI.
placementdrives.jobDescription: Build highly scalable systems for Amazon retail and AWS.

placementdrives.companyDescription: Adobe Inc. is a multinational software company focused on creativity and digital marketing solutions.
placementdrives.jobDescription: Work on Creative Cloud, Document Cloud, and Experience Cloud products.

placementdrives.companyDescription: Cisco Systems develops networking hardware, software, and telecommunications equipment.
placementdrives.jobDescription: Develop next-generation networking solutions and security products.

alumniinsights.experience: The interview process was intense but fair. Focus heavily on LeetCode hard problems, especially dynamic programming and graphs. System design round was unexpected for fresh grads.

rounds.name: HR Round
questions: Tell me about a challenging project

alumniinsights.experience: Azure-related questions and system design were the highlights. They really test your problem-solving approach more than getting the perfect solution.
Leadership Principles are EVERYTHING at Amazon. Every single answer should demonstrate at least one LP. Prepare STAR method stories.
preparationTips: Solve Amazon tagged problems on LeetCode

alumniinsights.experience: Very chill interview experience compared to FAANG. Focus on OOPS and clean code. They love creative problem solvers.
Expect puzzles and probability questions along with DSA. They test your analytical thinking extensively.
Strong focus on networking concepts. If you're from ECE, you have an advantage. Practice CCNA level concepts.
InfyTQ is key. If you clear it with good score, interview is mostly a formality. Focus on their training platform.
Their coding test is unique - 3 hour single problem that requires complete solution. Practice complete implementations.
preparationTips: Focus on implementation, not just logic
